Response ID: resp_1097
Response Text: More cultural heritage programming rooted in community! We need more opportunities for active, place-based engagement — especially events that bring people together across generations and cultures. Social dance is one of the most powerful tools for this: it’s interactive, joyful, and community-led. In my opinion, this is one of the longest-lasting forms of cultural heritage — and it also has the lowest barrier to entry and cost or risk to produce. I’d love to see more events where families and hundreds of neighbors can gather around live music, dance, food, and visual art all in one shared space.

